# The five built-in drivers

| Driver | What | When |
|---|---|---|
| **`bridge`** | private IP on a host bridge; NAT out, `-p` in | **~99% single-host** |
| **`host`** | shares host's net namespace, no isolation | max throughput, raw sockets |
| **`none`** | only `lo`, no connectivity | sandbox, forensics |
| **`overlay`** | one net across **many hosts** (VXLAN) | Swarm (module 09) |
| **`macvlan`/`ipvlan`** | own MAC/IP on the **physical LAN** | legacy LAN, IoT — niche |

**`bridge` is the workhorse** — private IP, NAT out, publish in — assume it unless a need pushes you off.

`host` / `none` are the two extremes (all of the host's net, or none); `overlay` / `macvlan` are multi-host and physical-LAN.

Next: the extremes (`host`/`none`), then publishing on `bridge`, then `overlay`/`macvlan`.
